# Server & API Routes

- Single `server.ts` file at project root — keep it self-contained
- Uses `tsx` to run TypeScript directly (no compilation step)
- In production, serves Vite build from `dist/`

## API routes

- `POST /api/transform` — Claude (Anthropic SDK) transforms prompt → editorial JSON
- `POST /api/generate` — Gemini 3 Pro Image (Google GenAI SDK) generates image from `prompt_compiled`

## Gemini image generation

Uses `generateContent` (NOT `generateImages`) with the Nano Banana Pro model:

```typescript
const response = await genai.models.generateContent({
  model: "gemini-3-pro-image-preview",
  contents: prompt_compiled,
  config: {
    responseModalities: ["TEXT", "IMAGE"],
    imageConfig: {
      aspectRatio: "16:9",
      imageSize: "2K",
    },
  },
});
```

Image is extracted from `response.candidates[0].content.parts` where `part.inlineData` exists.

## Environment variables

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — required for Claude
- `GEMINI_API_KEY` — required for Gemini
- `GEMINI_IMAGE_MODEL` — optional override (default: `gemini-3-pro-image-preview`)
- `PORT` — server port (default: 3001, Railway assigns automatically)

## Claude response parsing

Always strip markdown fences before parsing:

```typescript
let jsonText = textBlock.text.trim();
if (jsonText.startsWith("```")) {
  jsonText = jsonText.replace(/^```(?:json)?\n?/, "").replace(/\n?```$/, "");
}
const data = JSON.parse(jsonText);
```
